definitions.definition: ( chiefly historical ) A historical region of Western Europe referring to areas occupied by Celts during Roman times, roughly corresponding to modern France , Luxembourg , Belgium , most of Switzerland , and parts of Northern Italy ( Lombardy ), the Netherlands , and Germany west of the Rhine .

main_definition: ( chiefly historical ) A historical region of Western Europe referring to areas occupied by Celts during Roman times, roughly corresponding to modern France , Luxembourg , Belgium , most of Switzerland , and parts of Northern Italy ( Lombardy ), the Netherlands , and Germany west of the Rhine .

definitions.definition: A native or inhabitant of the historical region of Gaul, or poetically the modern nation of France .

main_definition: A native or inhabitant of the historical region of Gaul, or poetically the modern nation of France .
